I'd say generally:
>sapient
>relatively humanoid shape
>bipedal
>capable of carrying out a conversation
>non-human body
>head and face capable of conveying emotion and not entirely animalistic
>capable of using at least simple tools
>is clearly some species of non-human animal that meets all the above criteria
Disabilities and other such things are not counted when assessing these rules. A waifur will still be a waifur even if she lost her legs in a car crash and is currently in a coma.
